      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a pretty strong stance. But what about the people who argue that the \"living constitution\" approach is better? They claim that the Founders couldn't have envisioned modern weaponry and that the court's current view is actually ignoring how society has evolved. Why is their perspective considered \"activism\" while the other way is \"correct\"?",
